#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="mn8"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn8:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 8 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 8 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn8:0.2"
msgid "Sallekhasutta "
msgstr "Self-Effacement "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, sc1
msgctxt "mn8:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn8:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn8:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā mahācundo sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā mahācundo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Mahācunda came out of retreat and went to the Buddha. He bowed, sat down to one side, and said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3
msgctxt "mn8:3.1"
msgid "“yā imā, bhante, anekavihitā diṭṭhiyo loke uppajjanti—"
msgstr "“Sir, there are many different views that arise in the world "

msgctxt "mn8:3.2"
msgid "attavādapaṭisaṃyuttā vā lokavādapaṭisaṃyuttā vā—"
msgstr "connected with doctrines of the self or with doctrines of the cosmos. "

# NOTE: This question is a little curiously phrased in the Pali, and I suspect some corruption. The idiom adimeva occurs several times in the Samyutta (SN 47.15, etc.), where it refers to a mendicant purifying the “starting point” of kusala dhamma, i.e. sila and ditthi. Since ditthi are also spoken of here, the context must be the same. Thus BB following the comm errs in inserting “meditative training” here, as this “adi” is specifically said to precede meditation, as indeed it does in this sutta. (Neither MA 91 nor EA 47.9 appears to have close parallel to this phrase) This is just the start of the comm’s systematic misinterpretation of this sutta. Further, the question must be “how” this is done, as that is the answer the Buddha gives. Both Chinese texts have 云何 here, which typically stands for katham = how?
msgctxt "mn8:3.3"
msgid "ādimeva nu kho, bhante, bhikkhuno manasikaroto evametāsaṃ diṭṭhīnaṃ pahānaṃ hoti, evametāsaṃ diṭṭhīnaṃ paṭinissaggo hotī”ti? "
msgstr "How does a mendicant who is focusing on the starting point give up and let go of these views?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "mn8:3.4"
msgid "“Yā imā, cunda, anekavihitā diṭṭhiyo loke uppajjanti—"
msgstr "“Cunda, there are many different views that arise in the world "

msgctxt "mn8:3.5"
msgid "attavādapaṭisaṃyuttā vā lokavādapaṭisaṃyuttā vā—"
msgstr "connected with doctrines of the self or with doctrines of the cosmos. "

msgctxt "mn8:3.6"
msgid "yattha cetā diṭṭhiyo uppajjanti yattha ca anusenti yattha ca samudācaranti taṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na me so attā’ti—evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññā passato evametāsaṃ diṭṭhīnaṃ pahānaṃ hoti, evametāsaṃ diṭṭhīnaṃ paṭinissaggo hoti. "
msgstr "A mendicant gives up and lets go of these views by truly seeing with right wisdom where they arise, where they settle in, and where they operate as: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4, pts-vp-pli1.41, sc3
msgctxt "mn8:4.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ idhekacco bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihareyya. "
msgstr "It’s possible that a certain mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, might enter and remain in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "mn8:4.2"
msgid "Tassa evamassa: "
msgstr "They might think "

msgctxt "mn8:4.3"
msgid "‘sallekhena viharāmī’ti. "
msgstr "they’re practicing self-effacement. "

msgctxt "mn8:4.4"
msgid "Na kho panete, cunda, ariyassa vinaye sallekhā vuccanti. "
msgstr "But in the training of the noble one these are not called ‘self-effacement’; "

msgctxt "mn8:4.5"
msgid "Diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārā ete ariyassa vinaye vuccanti. "
msgstr "they’re called ‘blissful meditations in the present life’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5, sc4
msgctxt "mn8:5.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ idhekacco bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihareyya. "
msgstr "It’s possible that some mendicant, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, might enter and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "mn8:5.2"
msgid "Tassa evamassa: "
msgstr "They might think "

msgctxt "mn8:5.3"
msgid "‘sallekhena viharāmī’ti. "
msgstr "they’re practicing self-effacement. "

msgctxt "mn8:5.4"
msgid "Na kho panete, cunda, ariyassa vinaye sallekhā vuccanti. "
msgstr "But in the training of the noble one these are not called ‘self-effacement’; "

msgctxt "mn8:5.5"
msgid "Diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārā ete ariyassa vinaye vuccanti. "
msgstr "they’re called ‘blissful meditations in the present life’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6, sc5
msgctxt "mn8:6.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ idhekacco bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca vihareyya, sato ca sampajāno sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeyya, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihareyya. "
msgstr "It’s possible that some mendicant, with the fading away of rapture, might enter and remain in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’ "

msgctxt "mn8:6.2"
msgid "Tassa evamassa: "
msgstr "They might think "

msgctxt "mn8:6.3"
msgid "‘sallekhena viharāmī’ti. "
msgstr "they’re practicing self-effacement. "

msgctxt "mn8:6.4"
msgid "Na kho panete, cunda, ariyassa vinaye sallekhā vuccanti. "
msgstr "But in the training of the noble one these are not called ‘self-effacement’; "

msgctxt "mn8:6.5"
msgid "Diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārā ete ariyassa vinaye vuccanti. "
msgstr "they’re called ‘blissful meditations in the present life’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya7, sc6
msgctxt "mn8:7.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ idhekacco bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihareyya. "
msgstr "It’s possible that some mendicant, with the giving up of pleasure and pain, and the ending of former happiness and sadness, might enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness. "

msgctxt "mn8:7.2"
msgid "Tassa evamassa: "
msgstr "They might think "

msgctxt "mn8:7.3"
msgid "‘sallekhena viharāmī’ti. "
msgstr "they’re practicing self-effacement. "

msgctxt "mn8:7.4"
msgid "Na kho panete, cunda, ariyassa vinaye sallekhā vuccanti. "
msgstr "But in the training of the noble one these are not called ‘self-effacement’; "

msgctxt "mn8:7.5"
msgid "Diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārā ete ariyassa vinaye vuccanti. "
msgstr "they’re called ‘blissful meditations in the present life’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya8, sc7
msgctxt "mn8:8.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ idhekacco bhikkhu sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā, paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā, nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā, ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja vihareyya. "
msgstr "It’s possible that some mendicant, going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, might enter and remain in the dimension of infinite space. "

msgctxt "mn8:8.2"
msgid "Tassa evamassa: "
msgstr "They might think "

msgctxt "mn8:8.3"
msgid "‘sallekhena viharāmī’ti. "
msgstr "they’re practicing self-effacement. "

msgctxt "mn8:8.4"
msgid "Na kho panete, cunda, ariyassa vinaye sallekhā vuccanti. "
msgstr "But in the training of the noble one these are not called ‘self-effacement’; "

msgctxt "mn8:8.5"
msgid "Santā ete vihārā ariyassa vinaye vuccanti. "
msgstr "they’re called ‘peaceful meditations’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya9, sc8
msgctxt "mn8:9.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ idhekacco bhikkhu sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja vihareyya. "
msgstr "It’s possible that some mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, might enter and remain in the dimension of infinite consciousness. "

msgctxt "mn8:9.2"
msgid "Tassa evamassa: "
msgstr "They might think "

msgctxt "mn8:9.3"
msgid "‘sallekhena viharāmī’ti. "
msgstr "they’re practicing self-effacement. "

msgctxt "mn8:9.4"
msgid "Na kho panete, cunda, ariyassa vinaye sallekhā vuccanti. "
msgstr "But in the training of the noble one these are not called ‘self-effacement’; "

msgctxt "mn8:9.5"
msgid "Santā ete vihārā ariyassa vinaye vuccanti. "
msgstr "they’re called ‘peaceful meditations’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya10, sc9
msgctxt "mn8:10.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ idhekacco bhikkhu sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja vihareyya. "
msgstr "It’s possible that some mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, might enter and remain in the dimension of nothingness. "

msgctxt "mn8:10.2"
