#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "mn8:11.6"
msgid "1. Sallekhapariyāya "
msgstr "1. The Exposition of Self-Effacement "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: nya12, sc11
msgctxt "mn8:12.1"
msgid "Idha kho pana vo, cunda, sallekho karaṇīyo. "
msgstr "Now, Cunda, you should work on self-effacement in each of the following ways. "

# NOTE: The idiom here with “sallekho karaniyo” is strikingly reminiscent of the sekhiyas in the Vinaya, each of which ends with sikkha karaniya
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "mn8:12.2"
msgid "‘Pare vihiṃsakā bhavissanti, mayamettha avihiṃsakā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (1) "
msgstr "‘Others will be cruel, but here we will not be cruel.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "mn8:12.3"
msgid "‘Pare pāṇātipātī bhavissanti, mayamettha pāṇātipātā paṭiviratā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (2) "
msgstr "‘Others will kill living creatures, but here we will not kill living creatures.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "mn8:12.4"
msgid "‘Pare adinnādāyī bhavissanti, mayamettha adinnādānā paṭiviratā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (3) "
msgstr "‘Others will steal, but here we will not steal.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "mn8:12.5"
msgid "‘Pare abrahmacārī bhavissanti, mayamettha brahmacārī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (4) "
msgstr "‘Others will be unchaste, but here we will not be unchaste.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "mn8:12.6"
msgid "‘Pare musāvādī bhavissanti, mayamettha musāvādā paṭiviratā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (5) "
msgstr "‘Others will lie, but here we will not lie.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
#. VAR: pisuṇavācā → pisuṇāvācā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn8:12.7"
msgid "‘Pare pisuṇavācā bhavissanti, mayamettha pisuṇāya vācāya paṭiviratā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (6) "
msgstr "‘Others will speak divisively, but here we will not speak divisively.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
#. VAR: pharusavācā → pharusāvācā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn8:12.8"
msgid "‘Pare pharusavācā bhavissanti, mayamettha pharusāya vācāya paṭiviratā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (7) "
msgstr "‘Others will speak harshly, but here we will not speak harshly.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "mn8:12.9"
msgid "‘Pare samphappalāpī bhavissanti, mayamettha samphappalāpā paṭiviratā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (8) "
msgstr "‘Others will talk nonsense, but here we will not talk nonsense.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "mn8:12.10"
msgid "‘Pare abhijjhālū bhavissanti, mayamettha anabhijjhālū bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (9) "
msgstr "‘Others will be covetous, but here we will not be covetous.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "mn8:12.11"
msgid "‘Pare byāpannacittā bhavissanti, mayamettha abyāpannacittā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (10) "
msgstr "‘Others will have ill will, but here we will not have ill will.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc22
msgctxt "mn8:12.12"
msgid "‘Pare micchādiṭṭhī bhavissanti, mayamettha sammādiṭṭhī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (11) "
msgstr "‘Others will have wrong view, but here we will have right view.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc23
msgctxt "mn8:12.13"
msgid "‘Pare micchāsaṅkappā bhavissanti, mayamettha sammāsaṅkappā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (12) "
msgstr "‘Others will have wrong thought, but here we will have right thought.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc24
msgctxt "mn8:12.14"
msgid "‘Pare micchāvācā bhavissanti, mayamettha sammāvācā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (13) "
msgstr "‘Others will have wrong speech, but here we will have right speech.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc25
msgctxt "mn8:12.15"
msgid "‘Pare micchākammantā bhavissanti, mayamettha sammākammantā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (14) "
msgstr "‘Others will have wrong action, but here we will have right action.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc26
msgctxt "mn8:12.16"
msgid "‘Pare micchāājīvā bhavissanti, mayamettha sammāājīvā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (15) "
msgstr "‘Others will have wrong livelihood, but here we will have right livelihood.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc27
msgctxt "mn8:12.17"
msgid "‘Pare micchāvāyāmā bhavissanti, mayamettha sammāvāyāmā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (16) "
msgstr "‘Others will have wrong effort, but here we will have right effort.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc28
msgctxt "mn8:12.18"
msgid "‘Pare micchāsatī bhavissanti, mayamettha sammāsatī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (17) "
msgstr "‘Others will have wrong mindfulness, but here we will have right mindfulness.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc29
msgctxt "mn8:12.19"
msgid "‘Pare micchāsamādhi bhavissanti, mayamettha sammāsamādhī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (18) "
msgstr "‘Others will have wrong immersion, but here we will have right immersion.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc30
msgctxt "mn8:12.20"
msgid "‘Pare micchāñāṇī bhavissanti, mayamettha sammāñāṇī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (19) "
msgstr "‘Others will have wrong knowledge, but here we will have right knowledge.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc31
msgctxt "mn8:12.21"
msgid "‘Pare micchāvimuttī bhavissanti, mayamettha sammāvimuttī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (20) "
msgstr "‘Others will have wrong freedom, but here we will have right freedom.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc32
msgctxt "mn8:12.22"
msgid "‘Pare thinamiddhapariyuṭṭhitā bhavissanti, mayamettha vigatathinamiddhā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (21) "
msgstr "‘Others will be overcome with dullness and drowsiness, but here we will be rid of dullness and drowsiness.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc33
msgctxt "mn8:12.23"
msgid "‘Pare uddhatā bhavissanti, mayamettha anuddhatā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (22) "
msgstr "‘Others will be restless, but here we will not be restless.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc34
#. VAR: vicikicchī → vecikicchī (bj, s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn8:12.24"
msgid "‘Pare vicikicchī bhavissanti, mayamettha tiṇṇavicikicchā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (23) "
msgstr "‘Others will have doubts, but here we will have gone beyond doubt.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc35
msgctxt "mn8:12.25"
msgid "‘Pare kodhanā bhavissanti, mayamettha akkodhanā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (24) "
msgstr "‘Others will be irritable, but here we will be without anger.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc36
msgctxt "mn8:12.26"
msgid "‘Pare upanāhī bhavissanti, mayamettha anupanāhī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (25) "
msgstr "‘Others will be hostile, but here we will be without hostility.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.43, sc37
msgctxt "mn8:12.27"
msgid "‘Pare makkhī bhavissanti, mayamettha amakkhī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (26) "
msgstr "‘Others will be offensive, but here we will be inoffensive.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc38
msgctxt "mn8:12.28"
msgid "‘Pare paḷāsī bhavissanti, mayamettha apaḷāsī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (27) "
msgstr "‘Others will be contemptuous, but here we will be without contempt.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc39
msgctxt "mn8:12.29"
msgid "‘Pare issukī bhavissanti, mayamettha anissukī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (28) "
msgstr "‘Others will be jealous, but here we will be without jealousy.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc40
msgctxt "mn8:12.30"
msgid "‘Pare maccharī bhavissanti, mayamettha amaccharī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (29) "
msgstr "‘Others will be stingy, but here we will be without stinginess.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc41
msgctxt "mn8:12.31"
msgid "‘Pare saṭhā bhavissanti, mayamettha asaṭhā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (30) "
msgstr "‘Others will be devious, but here we will not be devious.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc42
msgctxt "mn8:12.32"
msgid "‘Pare māyāvī bhavissanti, mayamettha amāyāvī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (31) "
msgstr "‘Others will be deceitful, but here we will not be deceitful.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc43
msgctxt "mn8:12.33"
msgid "‘Pare thaddhā bhavissanti, mayamettha atthaddhā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (32) "
msgstr "‘Others will be stubborn, but here we will not be stubborn.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc44
msgctxt "mn8:12.34"
msgid "‘Pare atimānī bhavissanti, mayamettha anatimānī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (33) "
msgstr "‘Others will be arrogant, but here we will not be arrogant.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc45
msgctxt "mn8:12.35"
msgid "‘Pare dubbacā bhavissanti, mayamettha suvacā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (34) "
msgstr "‘Others will be hard to admonish, but here we will not be hard to admonish.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc46
msgctxt "mn8:12.36"
msgid "‘Pare pāpamittā bhavissanti, mayamettha kalyāṇamittā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (35) "
msgstr "‘Others will have bad friends, but here we will have good friends.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc47
msgctxt "mn8:12.37"
msgid "‘Pare pamattā bhavissanti, mayamettha appamattā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (36) "
msgstr "‘Others will be negligent, but here we will be diligent.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc48
msgctxt "mn8:12.38"
msgid "‘Pare assaddhā bhavissanti, mayamettha saddhā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (37) "
msgstr "‘Others will be faithless, but here we will have faith.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc49
msgctxt "mn8:12.39"
msgid "‘Pare ahirikā bhavissanti, mayamettha hirimanā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (38) "
msgstr "‘Others will be conscienceless, but here we will have a sense of conscience.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc50
#. VAR: anottāpī → anottappī (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "mn8:12.40"
msgid "‘Pare anottāpī bhavissanti, mayamettha ottāpī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (39) "
msgstr "‘Others will be imprudent, but here we will be prudent.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc51
msgctxt "mn8:12.41"
msgid "‘Pare appassutā bhavissanti, mayamettha bahussutā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (40) "
msgstr "‘Others will be uneducated, but here we will be well educated.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc52
msgctxt "mn8:12.42"
msgid "‘Pare kusītā bhavissanti, mayamettha āraddhavīriyā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (41) "
msgstr "‘Others will be lazy, but here we will be energetic.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc53
msgctxt "mn8:12.43"
msgid "‘Pare muṭṭhassatī bhavissanti, mayamettha upaṭṭhitassatī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (42) "
msgstr "‘Others will be unmindful, but here we will be mindful.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc54
msgctxt "mn8:12.44"
msgid "‘Pare duppaññā bhavissanti, mayamettha paññāsampannā bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (43) "
msgstr "‘Others will be witless, but here we will be accomplished in wisdom.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc55
msgctxt "mn8:12.45"
msgid "‘Pare sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggī bhavissanti, mayamettha asandiṭṭhiparāmāsī anādhānaggāhī suppaṭinissaggī bhavissāmā’ti sallekho karaṇīyo. (44) "
msgstr "‘Others will be attached to their own views, holding them tight, and refusing to let go, but here we will not be attached to our own views, not holding them tight, but will let them go easily.’ "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "mn8:12.46"
msgid "2. Cittupapādapariyāya "
msgstr "2. Giving Rise to the Thought "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: nya13, sc56
#. VAR: bahukāraṃ → bahūpakāraṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn8:13.1"
msgid "Cittuppādampi kho ahaṃ, cunda, kusalesu dhammesu bahukāraṃ vadāmi, ko pana vādo kāyena vācāya anuvidhīyanāsu. "
msgstr "Cunda, I say that even giving rise to the thought of skillful qualities is very helpful, let alone following that path in body and speech. "

msgctxt "mn8:13.2"
msgid "Tasmātiha, cunda, ‘pare vihiṃsakā bhavissanti, mayamettha avihiṃsakā bhavissāmā’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s why you should give rise to the following thoughts. ‘Others will be cruel, but here we will not be cruel.’ "

msgctxt "mn8:13.3"
msgid "‘Pare pāṇātipātī bhavissanti, mayamettha pāṇātipātā paṭiviratā bhavissāmā’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "‘Others will kill living creatures, but here we will not kill living creatures.’ … "

msgctxt "mn8:13.4"
msgid "‘pare sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggī bhavissanti, mayamettha asandiṭṭhiparāmāsī anādhānaggāhī suppaṭinissaggī bhavissāmā’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ. (44) "
msgstr "‘Others will be attached to their own views, holding them tight, and refusing to let go, but here we will not be attached to our own views, not holding them tight, but will let them go easily.’ "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "mn8:13.5"
msgid "3. Parikkamanapariyāya "
msgstr "3. A Way Around "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: nya14, pts-vp-pli1.44, sc57
#. VAR: assa, tassa → maggo tassāssa (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn8:14.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, cunda, visamo maggo assa, tassa añño samo maggo parikkamanāya; "
msgstr "Cunda, suppose there was a rough path and another smooth path to get around it. "

msgctxt "mn8:14.2"
msgid "seyyathā vā pana, cunda, visamaṃ titthaṃ assa, tassa aññaṃ samaṃ titthaṃ parikkamanāya; "
msgstr "Or suppose there was a rough ford and another smooth ford to get around it. "

msgctxt "mn8:14.3"
msgid "evameva kho, cunda, vihiṃsakassa purisapuggalassa avihiṃsā hoti parikkamanāya, pāṇātipātissa purisapuggalassa pāṇātipātā veramaṇī hoti parikkamanāya, adinnādāyissa purisapuggalassa adinnādānā veramaṇī hoti parikkamanāya, abrahmacārissa purisapuggalassa abrahmacariyā veramaṇī hoti parikkamanāya, musāvādissa purisapuggalassa musāvādā veramaṇī hoti parikkamanāya, pisuṇavācassa purisapuggalassa pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇī hoti parikkamanāya, pharusavācassa purisapuggalassa pharusāya vācāya veramaṇī hoti parikkamanāya, samphappalāpissa purisapuggalassa samphappalāpā veramaṇī hoti parikkamanāya, abhijjhālussa purisapuggalassa anabhijjhā hoti parikkamanāya, byāpannacittassa purisapuggalassa abyāpādo hoti parikkamanāya. (1–10.) "
msgstr "In the same way, a cruel individual gets around it by not being cruel. An individual who kills gets around it by not killing. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc58
msgctxt "mn8:14.4"
msgid "Micchādiṭṭhissa purisapuggalassa sammādiṭṭhi hoti parikkamanāya, micchāsaṅkappassa purisapuggalassa sammāsaṅkappo hoti parikkamanāya, micchāvācassa purisapuggalassa sammāvācā hoti parikkamanāya, micchākammantassa purisapuggalassa sammākammanto hoti parikkamanāya, micchāājīvassa purisapuggalassa sammāājīvo hoti parikkamanāya, micchāvāyāmassa purisapuggalassa sammāvāyāmo hoti parikkamanāya, micchāsatissa purisapuggalassa sammāsati hoti parikkamanāya, micchāsamādhissa purisapuggalassa sammāsamādhi hoti parikkamanāya, micchāñāṇissa purisapuggalassa sammāñāṇaṃ hoti parikkamanāya, micchāvimuttissa purisapuggalassa sammāvimutti hoti parikkamanāya. (11–20.) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc59
#. VAR: amāyā → amāyāvitā (mr)
msgctxt "mn8:14.5"
msgid "Thinamiddhapariyuṭṭhitassa purisapuggalassa vigatathinamiddhatā hoti parikkamanāya, uddhatassa purisapuggalassa anuddhaccaṃ hoti parikkamanāya, vicikicchissa purisapuggalassa tiṇṇavicikicchatā hoti parikkamanāya, kodhanassa purisapuggalassa akkodho hoti parikkamanāya, upanāhissa purisapuggalassa anupanāho hoti parikkamanāya, makkhissa purisapuggalassa amakkho hoti parikkamanāya, paḷāsissa purisapuggalassa apaḷāso hoti parikkamanāya, issukissa purisapuggalassa anissukitā hoti parikkamanāya, maccharissa purisapuggalassa amacchariyaṃ hoti parikkamanāya, saṭhassa purisapuggalassa asāṭheyyaṃ hoti parikkamanāya, māyāvissa purisapuggalassa amāyā hoti parikkamanāya, thaddhassa purisapuggalassa atthaddhiyaṃ hoti parikkamanāya, atimānissa purisapuggalassa anatimāno hoti parikkamanāya, dubbacassa purisapuggalassa sovacassatā hoti parikkamanāya, pāpamittassa purisapuggalassa kalyāṇamittatā hoti parikkamanāya, pamattassa purisapuggalassa appamādo hoti parikkamanāya, assaddhassa purisapuggalassa saddhā hoti parikkamanāya, ahirikassa purisapuggalassa hirī hoti parikkamanāya, anottāpissa purisapuggalassa ottappaṃ hoti parikkamanāya, appassutassa purisapuggalassa bāhusaccaṃ hoti parikkamanāya, kusītassa purisapuggalassa vīriyārambho hoti parikkamanāya, muṭṭhassatissa purisapuggalassa upaṭṭhitassatitā hoti parikkamanāya, duppaññassa purisapuggalassa paññāsampadā hoti parikkamanāya, sandiṭṭhiparāmāsiādhānaggāhiduppaṭinissaggissa purisapuggalassa asandiṭṭhiparāmāsianādhānaggāhisuppaṭinissaggitā hoti parikkamanāya. (21–44.) "
msgstr "An individual who is attached to their own views, holding them tight, and refusing to let go, gets around it by not being attached to their own views, not holding them tight, but letting them go easily. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "mn8:14.6"
msgid "4. Uparibhāgapariyāya "
msgstr "4. Going Up "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: nya15, pts-vp-pli1.45, sc60
msgctxt "mn8:15.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, cunda, ye keci akusalā dhammā sabbe te adhobhāgaṅgamanīyā, ye keci kusalā dhammā sabbe te uparibhāgaṅgamanīyā; "
msgstr "Cunda, all unskillful qualities lead downwards, while all skillful qualities lead upwards. "

#. VAR: uparibhāgāya → uparibhāvāya (bj, s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "mn8:15.2"
msgid "evameva kho, cunda, vihiṃsakassa purisapuggalassa avihiṃsā hoti uparibhāgāya, pāṇātipātissa purisapuggalassa pāṇātipātā veramaṇī hoti uparibhāgāya … pe … "
msgstr "In the same way, a cruel individual is led upwards by not being cruel. An individual who kills is led upwards by not killing … "

msgctxt "mn8:15.3"
msgid "sandiṭṭhiparāmāsiādhānaggāhiduppaṭinissaggissa purisapuggalassa asandiṭṭhiparāmāsianādhānaggāhisuppaṭinissaggitā hoti uparibhāgāya. (44) "
msgstr "An individual who is attached to their own views, holding them tight, and refusing to let go, is led upwards by not being attached to their own views, not holding them tight, but letting them go easily. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "mn8:15.4"
msgid "5. Parinibbānapariyāya "
msgstr "5. The Exposition by Extinguishment "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: nya16, sc61
msgctxt "mn8:16.1"
msgid "So vata, cunda, attanā palipapalipanno paraṃ palipapalipannaṃ uddharissatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "Truly, Cunda, if you’re sinking down in the mud you can’t pull out someone else who is also sinking down in the mud. "

msgctxt "mn8:16.2"
msgid "So vata, cunda, attanā apalipapalipanno paraṃ palipapalipannaṃ uddharissatīti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "But if you’re not sinking down in the mud you can pull out someone else who is sinking down in the mud. "

msgctxt "mn8:16.3"
msgid "So vata, cunda, attanā adanto avinīto aparinibbuto paraṃ damessati vinessati parinibbāpessatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "Truly, if you’re not tamed, trained, and extinguished you can’t tame, train, and extinguish someone else. "

msgctxt "mn8:16.4"
msgid "So vata, cunda, attanā danto vinīto parinibbuto paraṃ damessati vinessati parinibbāpessatīti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "But if you’re tamed, trained, and extinguished you can tame, train, and extinguish someone else. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn8:16.5"
msgid "Evameva kho, cunda, vihiṃsakassa purisapuggalassa avihiṃsā hoti parinibbānāya, pāṇātipātissa purisapuggalassa pāṇātipātā veramaṇī hoti parinibbānāya. "
msgstr "In the same way, a cruel individual extinguishes it by not being cruel. An individual who kills extinguishes it by not killing. … "

